wikipedia_page.main: Sir William Agnew, 1st Baronet (20 October 1825 – 31 October 1910) was an English politician and art dealer.  Thomas Agnew & Sons, his London art business in Mayfair flourished as one of the leading art dealerships in London from 1860, until it closed in April 2013, still with the Agnew family involved, and still known as "Agnew's Gallery", or more informally "Agnew's".
